Lateral aspect of podosoma
: Genal tooth broad, subrectangular, rounded distally, without dens ventrodistally, with longitudinal ridge ventrally (as for 
Fig. 2E
). Tutorium extending well anterior of rostrum; about 228 µm long, of which cusp about 144 µm long, rectangular, distal margin with about 10 dens. Custodium about 62 µm long, tapered (
Fig. 8
). Porose area Al about 21 µm in diameter.
